[254.956778, "o", "Predictions header: ['TransactionID', 'fraud_prob']\r\nPredictions sample row 2: [3108472, 0.4670987023462802] types: [<class 'int'>, <class 'float'>]\r\nData Quality Report contents:\r\n  total_train_rows: 8000 (type B=<class 'int'>)\r\n  total_test_rows: 2000 (type B=<class 'int'>)\r\n  shared_feature_count: 41 (type B=<class 'int'>)\r\n  model_auc_on_train_holdout: 0.5639305678140629 (type B=<class 'float'>)\r\nRow 6: ['issue_number', 'description', 'resolution']\r\n  Row 7: [1, 'Column naming mismatch between source systems: System A (train) uses underscore separators (e.g., id_01) while System B (test) uses hyphen separators (e.g., id-01).', \"Standardized the column names of System B (test) by replacing all hyphens with underscores, aligning them perfectly with System A's naming schema to enable consistent pipeline ingestion.\"]\r\n  Row 8: [2, 'High rate of missing values (NaNs) across features: There are 12 columns in train and 13 columns in test with missingness rates exceeding 50%.', \"Applied robust imputation strategies in the preprocessing pipeline: used median values for numerical columns and introduced a dedicated 'missing' string category for categorical columns.\"]\r\n  Row 9: [3, 'Inconsistent categorical levels (Out of Vocabulary values) in test features: Columns like id_30, id_31, id_33, id_34, and DeviceInfo contain unique categories in test not seen in train.', \"Configured scikit-learn OneHotEncoder with the 'handle_unknown=ignore' parameter to ensure the model pipeline processes unseen categorical values gracefully without causing errors or failures.\"]\r\n  Row 10: [4, \"Severe target class imbalance: The 'isFraud' target variable contains only 274 fraud cases (3.42%) out of 8,000 observations in the training dataset.\", \"Employed class-weighted loss adjustment ('class_weight=balanced') in Logistic Regression, and applied stratified splitting during holdout evaluation to ensure equal target distribution in splits.\"]\r\n"